# Web Development Projects

This repository contains multiple frontend projects built using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. The purpose of these projects is to demonstrate core web development concepts, UI structuring, and basic interactivity.

## Projects

### 1. Calculator
A basic calculator application that performs arithmetic operations such as addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division.

Key features:
- Clear (AC) and delete (DE) functionality  
- Decimal support  
- Interactive button-based input  

Tech stack:
HTML, CSS, JavaScript

### 2. Online Learning Platform (Kaksha)
A multi-section educational website interface designed to simulate an online learning platform.

Key features:
- Navigation bar with sections (Home, Courses, About, Contact)  
- Course listing section  
- Feature highlights (mock tests, doubt solving, etc.)  
- Footer with social media links  

Tech stack:
HTML, CSS

### 3. Course Registration Form
A structured form interface for enrolling in courses.

Key features:
- Input fields (name, email, password, phone)  
- Radio buttons, dropdown, and checkbox  
- Styled UI with focus and hover effects  

Tech stack:
HTML, CSS

### 4. Portfolio Website
A personal portfolio website showcasing profile, skills, projects, and contact details.

Key features:
- About section and skills visualization  
- Project links and resume access  
- Typing animation using JavaScript  
- Work experience timeline  

Tech stack:
HTML, CSS, JavaScript

## Concepts Covered

- HTML structure and semantic elements  
- CSS layout using Flexbox  
- Responsive design basics  
- JavaScript DOM manipulation  
- Event handling  
- UI/UX design fundamentals  

## How to Run

1. Clone the repository:
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/web-development-basics.git

2. Open any project folder

3. Run the HTML file in a browser

